# LIVECHAT

LiveChat is a full-stack application that allows you to send messages and chat with friends using chatengine.io .  It provides an easy way to set up a chat room and start messaging with friends you want.

## Getting Started

### Prerequisites

- Node.js and npm installed (https://nodejs.org/)
- Chatengine account, Project ID
 and Private Key (https://chatengine.io)

 ### Installation

1. Clone the repository:

   ```sh
   git clone https://github.com/AopnD/LiveChat.git

2. Navigate to the project directories:
Terminal 1
    cd backend
Terminal 2
    cd frontend
    

3. Install project dependencies:
    npm install

4. Create a .env file in backend dir containing the following variables.
 PROJECT_ID=<project_id_from_chatengine>
 PRIVATE_KEY=<private_key_from_chatengine>

5. Create a .env file in frontend dir containing the following variables.
VITE_AUTH_PAGE_CONFIG=</authenticate_url_path>
VITE_PROJECT_ID=<project_id_from_chatengine>

### Usage
1. in the backend terminal run npm start.
2. in the frontend terminal run npm run dev.
3. choose a username.
4. log in.
5. choose who to chat with.

### Testing
Run unit tests in the backend dir using Jest:
    npm test

